This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump at an event celebrating Hispanic Heritage Month at the White House. The President expressed his appreciation for the Hispanic American community and highlighted their contributions to the country. He discussed the achievements of Hispanic Americans in various fields, including business, the military, and law enforcement. The President also discussed his administration's policies, such as job creation, economic growth, and border security. He praised the work of Border Patrol and ICE agents and emphasized the importance of strong borders. The President also mentioned his efforts to promote religious liberty and democracy in the Western Hemisphere. The remarks also included testimonials from individuals who have made significant contributions to their communities, such as a small business owner and a pro-life advocate. The President concluded by expressing his pride in the Hispanic American community and reaffirming his commitment to making America greater than ever before.